bio.name: Natinael Samuel
bio.summary: A versatile full-stack software engineer with 5+ years of experience building web applications, SaaS platforms, AI solutions, and embedded systems. Skilled in frontend and backend technologies, database management, project management, and entrepreneurship. Founder of Diguwa-Store and Diguwa-Soft, leading multiple innovative projects in Ethiopia.

projects.description: First EMR system in Ethiopia, streamlining patient management and integrating with national ID.

projects.name: WZSIT-WebApp
projects.description: Tech support platform for Wolayita Zone integrating online appointments, real-time video consultations, and technical resources.

projects.name: St. Mary Finance Management System
projects.description: Cloud-based finance system automating accounting, reporting, and audits for parish operations.

projects.name: Wa-Leba & Wa-Leba+
projects.description: AI-driven business surveillance SaaS platform with intruder detection, trespassing alerts, and national-level security integration.

projects.name: Offline Book Store App

details: Started a dorm service platform connecting students to local businesses.
Scaled to 80+ daily visitors and revenue of 5,500 ETB in 2 months.
Developed cloud-based finance system and managed SQL architecture.
Developed expertise in AI, computer vision, and Three.js.
Led MedHub Ethiopia and other SaaS solutions.
